# RAG development

- Chunk documents by semantic boundaries (headings, paragraphs), not fixed character counts alone.
- Store chunk metadata: source, page, section, timestamp, access level.
- Use hybrid search (vector + BM25/keyword) for better recall on exact terms and names.
- Re-rank retrieved chunks before sending to the LLM (cross-encoder or lightweight reranker).
- Include source citations in responses; pass source IDs in context for traceability.
- Tune top-k and similarity thresholds with eval datasets — defaults rarely work.
- Refresh embeddings when documents or embedding models change.
- Monitor retrieval precision/recall separately from generation quality.
- Filter retrieved chunks by user permissions before LLM context injection.
- Keep the generation prompt separate from the retrieval query prompt.
